name: Frecciarossa
description:
Frecciarossa is a high-speed train of the Italian national train operator, Trenitalia, and a member of the train category Le Frecce. 

The name, which, if spelled "Freccia rossa" means "Red arrow" in English, was introduced in 2008 after it had previously been known as Eurostar Italia. 
Frecciarossa trains operate at speeds of up to 300 km/h (190 mph).
